quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Most Compassionate
  55,2,has taught the Qur’an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,and taught him speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon follow their precise courses
  55,6,"and the stars and trees prostrate [to Allah]"
  55,7,He raised the heaven and enjoined justice
  55,8,so that you may not transgress the limits of justice
  55,9,"Therefore establish weights in justice, and do not give short measure"
  55,10,He has spread out the earth for all creatures
  55,11,in which there are fruits and palm trees with date stalks
  55,12,"and grain having chaff, and fragrant plants"
  55,13,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,14,He created man from dry clay like pottery
  55,15,and He created the jinn from a smokeless flame of fire
  55,16,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,17,"[He is] Lord of the two sunrises and Lord of the two sunsets"
  55,18,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,19,"He merges the two seas [of fresh and salty water] meeting together"
  55,20,yet between them is a barrier so that they do not cross
  55,21,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,22,Out of both of them emerge pearls and coral
  55,23,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,24,To Him belong the sailing ships raised up in the sea like mountains
  55,25,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"